      "title": "Find the two constants",
      "content": "Substitute $(0,-13)$:\n$$r(0)+t(-13)=-65$$\n$$-13t=-65$$\n$$t=5$$\nSubstitute $(-10,-11)$ and $t=5$:\n$$-10r-11(5)=-65$$\n$$-10r= -10$$\n$$r=1$$"
    },
    {
      "title": "Add the constants",
      "content": "Now compute $r+t$:\n$$r+t=1+5=6$$\nThe answer is <strong>A</strong>."
